{
    "analysis": "From the file summaries we have: metric.csv (144k+ rows, 59 cmdb_id, 1152 KPI names) covering 2022-03-20 12:30:00+08 to 12:59:00+08; trace.csv (36k+ rows, 40 cmdb_id, 200 trace names) same time range; log.csv (1.8k rows) has two log metrics (log.error_count, log.row_count); error_logs.csv (1.99k rows) contains many warning messages from frontend-0/1/2 in the same time range. These suggest frontend warnings are present, but we must follow the workflow: compute global thresholds for all component-KPI series (using full series), then filter to the incident window (2022-03-20T12:30:00+08:00 through 2022-03-20T12:59:59+08:00) and detect anomalies. The next actionable step is to run a compact metric-level anomaly scan to surface top component-KPIs that breached global thresholds during the incident window (this will narrow down candidate faulty components/resources).",
